comment: Horford (ATL) establishes legal position during the rebounding engagement with Gortat (WAS).
Beal (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Teague's (ATL) driving layup attempt.
Horford (ATL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Wall (WAS) that does not affect his layup attempt.
Pierce (WAS) establishes himself in Horford's (ATL) path but Horford does not go through him on the pass and crash play in transition.
After Pierce (WAS) hands the ball off to Wall (WAS), the defending Carroll (ATL) runs into Pierce. The contact is initiated by Carroll and the screen by Pierce is legal.
Horford (ATL) sets the screen on Porter (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Korver (ATL) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
RATR shows that Gortat (WAS) dislodges Horford (ATL) from behind prior to the pass being thrown and affects his ability to defend the alley-oop.
Korver (ATL) sets the screen on Pierce (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Carroll (ATL) commits a take foul on Wall (WAS).
